<br />
Without knowing your equipment/focusy goodness, I can only presume to say this..  The Tier 3 named can't be appreciably harder than the Tier 4 normal INT casters.  My magelo will attest to the non-raid-quality gear I use, and I can (sweatingly) take out a T4 normal caster regularly.
<br />

<br />
By the way, exp is comparative to the exp in BoThunder when you're taking out Tier 4 normal mobs.   I dragged a bard, his botted cleric, a ranger and a druid (all similarly geared or slightly better with some LDoN gear) up there with me yesterday, and we didn't have any major problems, other than having to dodge around the 2 Paladin quest mobs.  Exp was very good, though oddly, no real armor or gem drops from the mobs.   We pulled to the courtyard NE of where Arch Lich T`Vaxok spawns (never saw him. grrr), had only one wanderer, which could have been avoided.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=559842" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dagard Ben`Shachar</a>
