			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>BalazarMagi wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Also interested here in if the book has a chance of dropping off lower teir named (like Magi P'Tasa)?  Thought I had read/heard somewhere that it has a very small chance...but cannot seem to find a yes or no answer now.  Any info?
<br />

<br />
Bal</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I can indeed confirm it rarely drops of Tier 1 int casters.  I got my Concordance of Black Magic off Coercer T'vala.  To maximize your chances, I suggest you go to just in front of where Lord of Loathing spawns, in that little corner where two buildings join (directly facing Avatar of Abhorrence's building).  You are safe at that point.  Then pull in the following order, doing one mob every four minutes or so:
<br />

<br />
1.  Roamer
<br />
2.  First one in Lord of Loathing's house.
<br />
3.  Lord of Loathing placeholder (or Lord).
<br />
4.  Third one in Lord of Loathing's house.
<br />
5.  First one in Coercer T'vala's house.
<br />
6.  Second one in Coercer T'vala's house.
<br />
7.  Coercer T'vala placeholder (or Coercer).
<br />

<br />
Med for two minutes, and roamer will respawn, then you just keep going in this pattern.  The reason you do the 3rd one in Loathing house is so there is absolutely no chance it will add inadvertantly when you get a Lord of Loathing (it usually doesn't but it did happen to me once).
<br />

<br />
I always use pet pull with pet discipline back to my camp point except when I get the actual Named, then I just rush him if I've gone through one cycle and can kill him with nothing else around.
<br />

<br />
The book is *extremely* rare (like 1 in 100 rare), but you also have a chance at getting a Shattered Emerald of Corruption, which with a little faction work even a Tier'dal can multiquest with a Ranger.  Also, yes book is rare, but that gem...drool.  It was SO worth it.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
